<p>A hovercraft is a vehicle that travels over land,water and other such surfaces on a cushion of air provided by a downward blast of air . They are now used throughout the world as specialized transports in disaster relief, coastguard service, and for sport or passenger service. The principal difference between a hovercraft and other amphibious vehicles is that a hovercraft can lift itself while still. It is available in all sizes as per the need .
